Brothers pizza has been in my rotation of pizza joints for a few years now, I can count on them to deliver a solid tasty pie that I’ll be satisfied with. Their extra cheese is legit but when I order from them I have to go with the breaded eggplant, not too many can get it right but Brothers Pizza definitely nails this one. They have curly fries too which are great, and so are the jalapeño poppers. Their baked ziti is great. Prices are great too! Can’t go wrong here!

I was looking for a good quality pizza from a local pizzeria. I found this place, it had over 4 stars and it was within 10 minutes of my location. I came in and reviewed the menu and opt to creating my own pizza. I ordered a simple sausage, peppers and onion pizza the wait was brief. When I got home I was surprised to find out the onions were raw and plentiful, susage cooked but sparse. I surprised as I paid 25 bucks, and apparently each topping is 4 bucks. Needless to say, I won't return, I was unsatisfied and ended up order dominos. You know it is bad when you opt for dominos when you have a 'fresh' in hand. I would not recommend, perhaps their prefix offerings are better.
